column2: b"API is really just a set of functions or procedures to do something within an application. Each application will have its own set of APIs. When application A wants to connect to application B to access its data, it will do so by calling application B's APIs. At this point is where the video's waiter analogy comes into play. When application A calls application B's API, the API is essentially functioning as a waiter--- sending a request to application B to grab some data and returning/delivering that data as a response to application A."
